When using View Transitions youâ€™ll notice the page becomes unresponsive to clicks while a View Transition is running. [â€¦] This happens because of theÂ Â pseudo element â€“ the one that contains all animated snapshots â€“ gets overlayed on top of the document and captures all the clicks.::view-transition /* ğŸ‘ˆ Captures all the clicks! */
â””â”€ ::view-transition-group(root)
   â””â”€ ::view-transition-image-pair(root)
      â”œâ”€ ::view-transition-old(root)
      â””â”€ ::view-transition-new(root)The trick? Itâ€™s that sneaky little  property! Slapping it directly on the  allows us to click â€œunderâ€ the pseudo-element, meaning the full page is interactive even while the view transition is running.::view-transition {
  pointer-events: none;
}I always, always,  forget about , so thanks to Bramus for posting this little snippet. I also appreciate the additional note about removing the  element from participating in the view transition::root {
  view-transition-name: none;
